This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various learning settings, such as supervised, weakly supervised, semi-supervised, and unsupervised, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of monolingual data, which is related to neural embeddings (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the quality of translations, which could be evaluated using computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
